      • getDataType

        default DataType getDataType()
                      throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Default implementation to create a payload or data to write/read. Default data type is byte[]. If your Benchmark type is other than byte[] then you need to implement your own Data class. If the data type of your Benchmark, Reader and Writer classes is byte[] (Byte Array), then use this default implementation as it is.
        Returns:
        Data Data interface, null in case of failure
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if data type is other than byte[]
